# lean-ctx — Shell hook compression (optional)

When the **lean-ctx shell hook** is active, Bash output is rewritten through compression patterns before the agent sees it. This is transparent — run normal Shell commands; no special MCP tools.

## What the hook does

- Rewrites `git`, `npm`, `cargo`, test runners, and similar CLI output to smaller summaries
- Does **not** replace Read, Grep, or Edit — use native Cursor tools for files
- Toggle: `lean-ctx-off` / `lean-ctx-on` in the shell

## When this rule applies

- `alwaysApply: false` — only relevant when you have enabled the lean-ctx hook in your environment
- If the hook is off, ignore this rule entirely

## Anti-patterns

- Do not assume `ctx_read`, `ctx_search`, `ctx_shell`, or other `ctx_*` MCP tools exist unless your environment explicitly provides them
- Do not skip native Read/Grep for file work because of this rule
